items.title: Moons of the Solar System
items.headline: Explore some of the most interesting bodies in the Solar System
objectives_summary: Many of the moons in our solar system are more interesting than some of the planets. We have found moons with oceans, volcanoes, geysers and earthquakes. There are moons that look like rocks, sponges and cheese. How many moons are there in the solar system? What is the difference between a moon and a planet? Take a trip around the solar system and see what the moons have to offer your curiosity.
Moons and their effects on planets
Moons in our Solar System

items.title: Stars of the Universe
items.headline: Stars as the building blocks of the unvierse
objectives_summary: Stars are the workhorses of the universe and account for most of its mass. They come in many shapes and sizes, some as small as just a few miles across and others that are as large as much of our solar system. Some are hundreds of times hotter than the Sun and others are just a few thousand degrees. When stars start running out of fuel they do some crazy things like explode into supernovae or implode into tightly packed white dwarfs or black holes.
How many stars are in the sky and how far are they?
Stars as the building blocks of the universe

items.title: Fundamentals of Double Hoop Tech
items.headline: Double Hoop Tech
objectives_summary: I have been working hard to create a comprehensive double hoop course that will provide you with all of the fundamental skills that you will need to create magic with your hoops. One of my goals in creating this course was to teach proper technique so that you will be equipped to learn and create anything you want to with double hoops. I reccomend everyone to review my Fundamentals of Double Hoop Tech Module before diving into the VTG/ WallPlane Pattern  Module. The Fundamentals of Double Hoop Tech will teach you all of the pre-requisites necessary for putting together Wall Plane Patterns with 2 hoops. You will also learn some drills and tricks that will help you do these fundamentals cleanly and with ease.
